body:
I have been playing LOL for about a year now with the same setup.  Nothing has changed and I normally play at around 40-60 ms every game.  Recently, for about a week now, I have been catching huge lag spikes, like 500+ms, and it occurs about every 30 seconds, making the game virtually unplayable.  It is very, very consistent.  The strange part is that my internet connection is still solid.  I can stream Netflix, music, Youtube, Twitch  all at once with no buffering.  It is just my connection within the game itself.  I'm always very cautious too to not have anything running in the background when I play.

I have tried some things like flushing my dns and I've even reinstalled the client thinking maybe it would help, but no dice.  Any insight or suggestions on the situation are greatly appreciated. It's just becoming increasingly frustrating. 
